                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/742: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia (<persName type="to">Werlich</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 14, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Your telegram No. 97, December 12, noon. We believe that our position has
                    been made so abundantly clear that for the present no further action need be
                    taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
